  "prompt": "What can substitute butter in a brownies recipe?",
  "response": "There are several substitutes for butter in a brownie recipe, depending on dietary needs and flavor preferences. Here are some options:\n\n1. **Oil**: Vegetable oil, canola oil, or coconut oil can be used as a direct substitute for butter. Use about 3/4 the amount of oil compared to the butter called for in the recipe.\n\n2. **Applesauce**: Unsweetened applesauce can work as a healthier alternative. Use a 1:1 ratio, but keep in mind that this may make the brownies slightly denser.\n\n3. **Nut Butters**: Almond butter, peanut butter, or other nut butters can be used for added flavor and healthy fats. Substitute in equal amounts, but be aware that it may alter the taste and texture.\n\n4. **Greek Yogurt**: For a lower-fat option, you can use plain Greek yogurt. Use about half the amount of yogurt as you would butter to maintain the right texture.\n\n5. **Margarine or Vegan Butter**: These can often be used as a 1:1 substitution for butter and will yield similar results.\n\n6. **Coconut Cream**: Full-fat coconut cream can add a rich flavor and moisture. Again, use it in equal amounts to butter.\n\n7. **Silken Tofu**: Pureed silken tofu can provide a creamy texture and is a great option for a vegan alternative. Replace butter with an equal amount of pureed tofu.\n\nChoose the substitute that best fits your dietary preferences and desired flavor outcome!",
